-- Gunfire heard near Turkish PM's office: TV
-- 
-- Mon Nov 5, 2012 7:39am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/11/05/us-turkey-gunfire-idUSBRE8A40KV20121105

 

 ANKARA  (Reuters) - The sound of gunfire was heard near the Turkish prime minister's office in Ankara on Monday as ministers convened for a cabinet meeting but there were no reports of casualties, Turkish media reported. 
 Broadcaster NTV said three shots had been fired but that they had been blank cartridges. It said one man had been detained in relation to the incident. (Writing by  Jonathon Burch ; Editing by Pravin Char)